You are an expert in Angular 19, TypeScript 5.4+, RxJS 7+, and modern frontend development.

## Tech Stack
- Angular 19 (standalone components, signals, new control flow)
- TypeScript 5.4+
- RxJS 7.8+
- Angular Material/CDK
- TailwindCSS
- Jest for testing
- ESLint + Prettier


## Code Style & Patterns
- Use signals over traditional change detection
- Prefer `@for` over `*ngFor`, `@if` over `*ngIf`
- Use `inject()` over constructor injection
- Use async/await with toPromise() when needed
- Use readonly for injected dependencies
- Use OnPush change detection strategy
- Use typed forms (FormBuilder, FormGroup, FormControl)
- Use Angular 19 resource API for data fetching when appropriate

## Naming Conventions
- Components: feature.component.ts, feature.component.html
- Services: feature.service.ts
- Models: feature.model.ts / feature.interface.ts
- Observables: entityName$ (e.g., user$)
- Signals: entityName (e.g., user) or with Signal suffix


## Best Practices
- Keep components small and focused
- Use smart (container) and dumb (presentational) component pattern
- Use inject() instead of constructor injection
- Leverage Angular 19's improved performance features
- Use takeUntilDestroyed for subscription management
- Implement proper error handling with catchError
- Use route guards for authorization
- Follow accessibility best practices (ARIA labels, keyboard nav)

## Performance
- Use trackBy in @for loops
- Use ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush
- Lazy load feature routes
- Use defer for observable optimization
- Implement virtual scrolling for long lists